    <statement><p>Simplify this expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{6y-24}{35+28y-7y^{2}}} \cdot {\frac{y^{2}-10y+25}{3y^{2}-12y}} =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{2\mathopen{}\left(y-5\right)}{7y\mathopen{}\left(y+1\right)}, y\ne 4\hbox{ and }y\ne 5</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{6y-24}{35+28y-7y^{2}}} \cdot {\frac{y^{2}-10y+25}{3y^{2}-12y}} 
      \amp = \frac{{6y-24}}{-7y^2 + 28y+35} \cdot {\frac{y^{2}-10y+25}{3y^{2}-12y}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{6\mathopen{}\left(y-4\right)}}{{-7\mathopen{}\left(y^{2}-4y-5\right)}} \cdot \frac{{\left(y-5\right)^{2}}}{{3y\mathopen{}\left(y-4\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{6\mathopen{}\left(y-4\right)}}{{-7\mathopen{}\left(y-5\right)\mathopen{}\left(y+1\right)}} \cdot \frac{{\left(y-5\right)^{2}}}{{3y\mathopen{}\left(y-4\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{2\mathopen{}\left(y-5\right)}{7y\mathopen{}\left(y+1\right)}, y\ne 4\hbox{ and }y\ne 5}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factors <m>y-4</m> and <m>y-5</m> were canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>y \ne {4, 5}</m>.</p>
</solution>
